Google has published the results of its 2019 Year in Search, providing insight into the year’s major moments and top trends based on searches conducted in South Africa. This year’s trending searches show South Africans’ keen interest in the world and people around them, Google said. “Pop culture, sports and politics captured the nation’s attention. Nine of the 10 top trending search terms were for local people, news and events. The top questions list reflects this strongly – with eight of the top ten questions related to local happenings. “From the Rugby World Cup to load shedding, elections and James Small, South Africans use search to find out about the things that really matter to them.” Below are some of the most notable search trends. Top trending questions <img class="aligncenter wp-image-350877 size-full" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Springboks0-e1572845305983.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="427" /> Top trending questions of the decade <img class="aligncenter wp-image-361348" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Cornflakes.jpeg" alt="" width="640" height="419" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Cornflakes.jpeg 2292w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Cornflakes-300x196.jpeg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Cornflakes-1024x670.jpeg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Cornflakes-768x503.jpeg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Cornflakes-1536x1005.jpeg 1536w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Cornflakes-2048x1340.jpeg 2048w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Cornflakes-1200x785.jpeg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Top 10 trending searches <img class="aligncenter wp-image-315170 size-full" src="https://businesstech.